    "hero-lead": {
      "type": "text",
      "variant": "lead",
      "props": {
        "content": "Graph intelligence = what the graph tells us about itself WITHOUT being told. Community detection finds clusters we didn't name. TopoNetX proves closure via Euler characteristic. Betweenness centrality surfaces bridges. Duplicate detection spots merges. sklearn predicts labels. Scope nesting enables hierarchical queries. Chirality enforces direction. The more sidecars, the more the graph earns its keep."
      }
    },
    "sec-what-is": {
      "type": "section",
      "variant": "stacked",
      "props": {
        "label": "CONCEPT",
        "title": "What Is Graph Intelligence?",
        "subtitle": "Seven forms of insight the graph computes about itself"
      },
      "children": [
        "gi-body",
        "gi-types"
      ]
    },
    "gi-body": {
      "type": "text",
      "variant": "prose",
      "props": {
        "content": "A dumb graph is a bag of nodes and edges you query with exact-match. A smart graph COMPUTES things about itself. Our skill graph has 155 nodes, 112 edges, and now runs 7 kinds of self-analysis on every rebuild. Each form of intelligence is a sidecar that reads the owner stack and writes a report to `~/.cache/lev/harness/skill-graph/`. None of them can write to the owner graph (per SIDECAR_POLICY.md), but they surface insights that shape human decisions."
      }
    },
    "gi-types": {
      "type": "text",
      "variant": "prose",
      "props": {
        "content": "**1. Topological validation** \u2014 TopoNetX computes Euler characteristic. If \u03c7 \u2260 4, a lane lost closure.\n\n**2. Community detection** \u2014 NetworkX Louvain/Label Prop/Greedy agree 95.10% on the 4-lane structure. No new clusters to discover.\n\n**3. Centrality analysis** \u2014 Betweenness centrality ranks nodes by how many paths pass through them. The bridges.\n\n**4. Duplicate detection** \u2014 difflib fuzzy matching surfaces merge candidates within the same lane.\n\n**5. Drift tracking** \u2014 `graph_diff.py` compares two snapshots and reports added/removed/changed.\n\n**6. Classification prediction** \u2014 sklearn TF-IDF + LogReg suggests lanes for unlabeled skills.\n\n**7. Scope traversal** \u2014 `nx.ancestors()` walks the `parent_id` chain: skill \u2192 lane \u2192 workstream \u2192 project."
      }
    },
